cs.DC, cs.CV, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the challenges of developing interactive and reusable data analytic tools on Big Data platforms such as Hadoop and Spark. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper presents a case study on modularizing real-world computation-intensive tasks for processing large-scale image data. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper discusses the challenges of accessing and controlling data flow among components when working with large-scale data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of modularization for computation-intensive tasks, which is a common technique in machine learning. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the challenges of developing interactive and reusable data analytic tools and proposes a modular model for effective implementation of computation-intensive tasks on data-parallel frameworks.
